---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy — NetSpeed Network Diagnostics"
  description="Review the NetSpeed privacy policy. Learn about telemetry data gathering, local cache bypass, and how we keep your diagnostics anonymous."
>
  <main class="flex-1 py-16 px-4 md:px-8">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto flex flex-col gap-10">
      {/* Header */}
      <div class="flex flex-col gap-3 border-b border-hairline pb-6">
        <span
          class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-wider text-mute block"
        >
          Compliance & Transparency
        </span>
        <h1
          class="text-3xl md:text-5xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-ink font-sans"
        >
          Privacy Policy.
        </h1>
        <p class="text-xs font-mono text-mute mt-1">
          LAST MODIFIED: JUNE 10, 2026
        </p>
      </div>

      {/* Main Content Layout */}
      <div
        class="flex flex-col gap-8 text-sm md:text-base text-body leading-relaxed"
      >
        <section class="flex flex-col gap-3">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-ink font-sans">
            1. Telemetry and connection diagnostics.
          </h2>
          <p>
            When you initiate a connection benchmark on NetSpeed, our platform
            temporarily gathers network-level telemetries. This includes your
            external Internet Protocol (IP) address, approximate geolocation
            (city, region, and country level), your Internet Service Provider
            (ISP) network name (ASN), and transit metrics such as download
            speeds, upload speeds, round-trip ping time, and packet jitter
            variables.
          </p>
          <p>
            These details are analyzed on-the-fly inside local worker threads
            and are displayed in your browser dashboard. Geolocation lookup is
            conducted entirely server-side in a secure runtime, and raw IPs are
            processed to output approximate coordinates for distance
            calculations.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="flex flex-col gap-3 border-t border-hairline pt-8">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-ink font-sans">
            2. Storage and persistence rules.
          </h2>
          <p>
            NetSpeed operates with a strict no-collection priority. We do not
            maintain databases tracking individual speed histories, name
            details, search profiles, or account contexts:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-5 flex flex-col gap-2 text-xs md:text-sm">
            <li>
              <strong>Connection Logs</strong>: Telemetry metrics captured
              during tests are ephemeral. We do not store log lines of speed
              tests permanently unless you choose to export them locally as a
              CSV output.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Cookies</strong>: We do not deploy third-party trackers,
              retargeting mechanisms, or profile trackers.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Local Storage</strong>: We use local storage variables
              (e.g. <code>theme</code>) to preserve preferences (like Light /
              Dark themes) client-side. This data remains on your machine and is
              never sent to our servers.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="flex flex-col gap-3 border-t border-hairline pt-8">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-ink font-sans">
            3. Data retention and sharing.
          </h2>
          <p>
            Because we do not store personal details, we do not trade, sell, or
            rent user diagnostic metrics to advertisers or research coalitions.
            Any aggregate diagnostic reports analyzed in memory are strictly
            utilized to assess regional routing efficiency and server
            utilization rates to optimize routing tables.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="flex flex-col gap-3 border-t border-hairline pt-8">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-ink font-sans">
            4. Adjustments and inquiries.
          </h2>
          <p>
            We reserve the right to modify this telemetry privacy declaration to
            conform to international data standards. If you have questions
            regarding our measurement pipeline or geoip analysis, please
            direct your questions through our <a
              href="/contact"
              class="text-link hover:underline">Contact page</a
            >.
          </p>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>
